{"schemaVersion":1,"book":"1TI","entries":[{"id":"rvr1960-notas-4995","title":"1 Timoteo 1:1–2","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":2},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Salutación</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-4996","title":"1 Timoteo 1:2","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":2,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":2},"content":"<p>a Timoteo,<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> verdadero hijo en la fe: Gracia, misericordia y paz, de Dios nuestro Padre y de Cristo Jesús nuestro Señor.</p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b44.16.1'>Hch 16:1</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-4997","title":"1 Timoteo 1:3–11","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":3,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":11},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Advertencia contra falsas doctrinas</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-4998","title":"1 Timoteo 1:12–20","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":12,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":20},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>El ministerio de Pablo</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-4999","title":"1 Timoteo 1:13","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":1,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":1,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p>habiendo yo sido antes blasfemo, perseguidor<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>b</sup></span></i></span> e injuriador; mas fui recibido a misericordia porque lo hice por ignorancia, en incredulidad.</p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>b</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b44.8.3'>Hch 8:3</a>; <a class='bible' href='#b44.9.4-5'>Hch 9:4-5</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5001","title":"1 Timoteo 2:7","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":7,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<p>Para esto yo fui constituido predicador y apóstol (digo verdad en Cristo, no miento), y maestro de los gentiles en fe y verdad.<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b55.1.11'>2Ti 1:11</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5002","title":"1 Timoteo 2:9","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":9,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":9},"content":"<p>Asimismo que las mujeres se atavíen de ropa decorosa, con pudor y modestia; no con peinado ostentoso, ni oro, ni perlas, ni vestidos costosos,<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>b</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>b</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b60.3.3'>1Pe 3:3</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5003","title":"1 Timoteo 2:13","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p>Porque Adán fue formado primero,<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>c</sup></span></i></span> después Eva;<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>d</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>c</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b1.2.7'>Gén 2:7</a>.</p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>d</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b1.2.21-22'>Gén 2:21-22</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5004","title":"1 Timoteo 2:14","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":14,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":14},"content":"<p>y Adán no fue engañado, sino que la mujer, siendo engañada, incurrió en transgresión.<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>e</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>e</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b1.3.1-6'>Gén 3:1-6</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5000","title":"1 Timoteo 2:15","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":2,"verseStart":15,"chapterEnd":2,"verseEnd":15},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Instrucciones sobre la oración</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5005","title":"1 Timoteo 3:1–7","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Requisitos de los obispos</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5006","title":"1 Timoteo 3:2–7","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":2,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":7},"content":"<p>También es necesario que tenga buen testimonio de los de afuera, para que no caiga en descrédito y en lazo del diablo.<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b56.1.6-9'>Tit 1:6-9</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5007","title":"1 Timoteo 3:8–13","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":8,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Requisitos de los diáconos</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5008","title":"1 Timoteo 3:14–16","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":3,"verseStart":14,"chapterEnd":3,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>El misterio de la piedad</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5009","title":"1 Timoteo 4:1–5","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":5},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Predicción de la apostasía</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5010","title":"1 Timoteo 4:6–16","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":4,"verseStart":6,"chapterEnd":4,"verseEnd":16},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Un buen ministro de Jesucristo</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5011","title":"1 Timoteo 5:1–25","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":5,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":5,"verseEnd":25},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Deberes hacia los demás</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5012","title":"1 Timoteo 5:18","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":5,"verseStart":18,"chapterEnd":5,"verseEnd":18},"content":"<p>Pues la Escritura dice: No pondrás bozal al buey que trilla;<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> y: Digno es el obrero de su salario.<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>b</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b5.25.4'>Deu 25:4</a>.</p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>b</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b40.10.10'>Mat 10:10</a>; <a class='bible' href='#b42.10.7'>Luc 10:7</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5013","title":"1 Timoteo 5:19","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":5,"verseStart":19,"chapterEnd":5,"verseEnd":19},"content":"<p>Contra un anciano no admitas acusación sino con dos o tres testigos.<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>c</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>c</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b5.17.6'>Deu 17:6</a>; <a class='bible' href='#b5.19.15'>Deu 19:15</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5014","title":"1 Timoteo 6:1–2","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":1,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":2},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Deberes hacia los demás</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5015","title":"1 Timoteo 6:3–10","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":3,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":10},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Piedad y contentamiento</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5016","title":"1 Timoteo 6:11–19","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":11,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":19},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>La buena batalla de la fe</b></p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5017","title":"1 Timoteo 6:13","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":13,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":13},"content":"<p>Te mando delante de Dios, que da vida a todas las cosas, y de Jesucristo, que dio testimonio de la buena profesión delante de Poncio Pilato,<span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span></p><p><span style=\"color: #804db3\"><i><span ><sup>a</sup></span></i></span> <a class='bible' href='#b43.18.37'>Jua 18:37</a>.</p>"},{"id":"rvr1960-notas-5018","title":"1 Timoteo 6:20–21","author":"Sociedades Bíblicas Unidas / EBH","reference":{"book":"1TI","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":20,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":21},"content":"<p><b><i>Tema:</i></b></p><p><b>Encargo final de Pablo a Timoteo</b></p>"}]}